latestPosts.caption:
In my unbothered era 👻
Happy Father’s Day to me — and to my younger self who decided, at 20, to take on this full-time job 🥲.

I’ve made some really questionable choices in life — but this wasn’t one of them.
Being both? The most powerful role I’ve ever stepped into.
Because at the end of the day, your child needs love — and only love.

To all the single parents or those still figuring it out:
	1.	Your child needs just one present, loving parent.
	2.	You’ll show up. You’ll provide. You’re already enough.
	3.	No one died from a divorce — but many suffer from staying too long.
	4.	Protect your child’s heart. That’s the real job.
	5.	Normalize different family dynamics.
	6.	Choose peace over a damaged childhood — every time.

You’re doing better than you think. 

Be better for you and your kids! You only get one life to make it worth living.
